  <Subject Subject_ID="300233715">
    <Parent_Relationships>
      <Preferred_Parent>
        <Parent_Subject_ID>300212828</Parent_Subject_ID>
        <Relationship_Type>Parent/Child</Relationship_Type>
        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>flatcars [300212828], freight cars by form [300228357], freight cars [300212993], railroad cars [300233722], rail guideway vehicles [300228410], guideway vehicles [300212494], land vehicles by form [300215717], land vehicles [300212968], vehicles (transportation) [300219258], Transportation Vehicles (hierarchy name) [300042929], Furnishings and Equipment (hierarchy name) [300264551], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Flatcars having a portion of the floor set lower than the deck to accommodate special loads with oversized vertical dimensions; in use since the early 20th century. For flatcars in use since the mid-20th century with larger depressed central sections designed primarily to accommodate intermodal containers, use "well cars."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Te gebruiken voor platte goederenwagons met verlaagde vloer om ruimte te bieden aan speciale ladingen van grote verticale afmetingen; in gebruik sinds het begin van de 20e eeuw. Gebruik 'well cars' voor platte goederenwagons met een groter dieper deel die vanaf halverwege de 20e eeuw worden gebruikt en vooral zijn ontworpen voor intermodale containers.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Flachwagen, bei dem ein Teil des Bodens tiefer gelegt ist als das Deck, um spezielle Ladungen mit übergroßer vertikaler Ausrichtung unterbringen zu können; seit Anfang des 20. Jahrhunderts in Gebrauch. Für den Flachwagen, der seit Mitte des 20. Jahrhunderts in Gebrauch ist, der mit größeren tiefer gelegten mittleren Abschnitten hauptsächlich für die Unterbringung von genormten Containern für den kombinierten Verkehr entworfen ist, siehe "Well Car".</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
